<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-12-03"><hi rend="italic">December 3,
                                    1890</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 93.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 180, of the 3d
                            ultimo, stating that the minister of finance had officially communicated
                            the claim of the Hydro-graphic Commission of the Amazon to Congress,
                            which had adjourned, however, without making the necessary appropriation
                            to pay the same.</p>
                        <p>The Department observes with satisfaction the progress thus made in this
                            long-pending claim, and sincerely hope that on the reassembling of
                            Congress in July next the Government of Peru may be enabled to obtain
                            without further delay the sum necessary to liquidate this just
                            demand.</p>
                        <p>You will give the matter attention in this sense at the proper time.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>